activities:
Time Inc. may collect and use Employee and Consumer Personal Data for the following purposes:

EMPLOYEE DATA.  Personal Data of Time Inc.’s and its subsidiaries’ current and former employees, other workers and vendors, their beneficiaries and dependents. 
o	For human resources functions, including administering employee contracts, employee evaluations, implementing employee-related actions and obligations and providing employment benefits and related information; compensation planning, including raises and bonuses/stock grants; 
o	Payment services for vendors;
o	Incident management, technology requests, change management;
o	Authentication.

CONSUMER DATA.  Personal Data of Time Inc.’s and its subsidiaries’ current, past, and prospective customers. 
o	Data warehousing for business intelligence, analytics, marketing, product distribution, customer retention and acquisition;
o	Order acceptance, subscription fulfillment, customer service, payment processing, retention marketing, and cancel processing for magazines, digital products, goods, and services;
o	User-generated content tools, including message boards and commenting;
o	Extending and managing magazine subscriber access to digital products; and
o	Online subscription sales.
